    {
        "url": "/quotes/per_petterson_685636",
        "quote": "To me, a book is a book. A novel is a novel, and you have hundreds of possibilities, options, and they may all be fine. Charles Dickens or Ingeborg Bachmann, Claude Simon or later writers. The one and only condition is that it has to be good: it has to have quality, substance, atmosphere.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Per Petterson",
            "url": "/quotes/per_petterson_685636"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Possibilities",
                "url": "/topics/possibilities"
